04964nam a22005175i 9780822395966DE-B159720201212080620.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||201212t19991999ncu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808223959667 a10.1515/97808223959662doi  a(DE-B1597)551907  a(OCoLC)1229161966  a(OCoLC)1226679030  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ancucUS-NC 4aPN1995.9.S284bS33 1999 7aPER0040302bisacsh1 aSchaefer, Eric, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aBold! Daring! Shocking! True! :bA History of Exploitation Films, 1919-1959 /cEric Schaefer. 1aDurham : bDuke University Press, c[1999] 4cÂ©1999  a1 online resource (488 p.) :b59 b&w photographs, 7 figures  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction: "As Long as It Was in Bad Taste!" -- t1. "An Attempt to 'Commercialize Vice''': Origins of the Exploitation Film -- t2. "A Hodge-Podge of Cuttings and Splicings": The Mode of Production and the Style of Classical Exploitation Films -- t3. "You Gotta Tell 'Em to Sell 'Em": Distribution, Advertising, and Exhibition of Exploitation Films -- t4. "Thoroughly Vile and Disgusting": The Exploitation Film and Censorship -- t5. "No False Modesty, No Old-Fashioned Taboos": The Sex Hygiene Film -- t6. "The Monster That Caters to Thrill-Hungry Youth": The Drug Film -- t7. "Timely as Today's Front Page": Vice, Exotic, and Atrocity Films -- t8. "They Wear No Clothes!": Nudist and Burlesque Films -- t9. Conclusion: The End of Classical Exploitation -- tAppendix 1-Major Exploitation Producers/Distributors and Their Company Names -- tAppendix 2-Filmogra -- tAppendix 3-Video Sources -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aUnashamed nudists, high-flying hopheads, brazen strippers, vicious vice lords, and high school girls who find themselves "in trouble" comprise the population of exploitation films. In the first full-scale history of these low-budget movies of decades past, Eric Schaefer reveals how this pioneering form of "trash film" purveyed the forbidden thrills of explicit sexual behavior, drug use, and vice that the mainstream movie industry could not show.Bold! Daring! Shocking! True! is a meticulously researched, interdisciplinary study that is informed by a wide range of sources-including both mainstream and industry newspapers and periodicals, archival accounts, personal interviews, and the films themselves. Schaefer begins by exploring the unique mode of production of exploitation movies, their distribution, and the outrageous exhibition practices that were rooted in the traditions of sideshows and carnivals. His close analysis of dozens of films, such as The Road to Ruin, Modern Motherhood, One Way Ticket to Hell, and The Wages of Sin demonstrates that these films were more than simply "bad" movies. By situating exploitation films in a historical context and organizing them according to the social problems they addressed, Schaefer shows how they evolved during a period of forty years and how, during that time, they shaped public policies and attitudes. Finally, he focuses on the changes in the postwar American film industry that led to the decline of the classical exploitation film and set the stage for the rise of "sexploitation" in the 1960s.Engagingly written, illustrated with rare photographs, posters, production stills, and ad slicks, and offering a full filmography, Bold! Daring! Shocking! True! reveals a forgotten side of film history and American culture. It will delight and inform those interested in film history, cultural studies, American studies and history, and the many fans of exploitation films.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aExploitation filmsxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822395966423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822395966.jpg  a978-3-11-071360-2  DUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles